Package solPicker.filters

Class Summary
BaseFractionFilter Calculates the percent distribution of each of the nucleotide bases, and filters oligos based on the equality of the distributions.
BlastFilter This class filters out oligos that are not unique and that do not have a good align length.
EnzymeFilter Often, enzymes are used to cleave the DNA sequences before applying them to the microarray.
FailScoreFilter This filter performs a series of operations on the oligos and assigns each a score based on these computations.
Filter The base class for all Filters.
GCFilter For a variety of reasons, many of them purely practical, an ideal oligo has a good balance of GC and AT base pairs.
HomoPolymerFilter This filter calculates the homopolymer score of each oligo.
LowerCaseFilter The program retrieves the specified sequences from online genome databases.
NCountFilter There are many areas of the genome that still have not been entirely sequenced, most notably the centromere and telemere regions of each chromosome.
TMFilter This filter discards oligos whose temperatures are not within a certain range, as specified by the user.
